modelVersions.name: v3.13
modelVersions.description:
Generate using a weight of 0.3-1 like this: <lora:KnottedShirtv313:0.7>.


How I archived my generations:

  1. txt2img: DPM++ SDE Karras with 20 steps, 512x512(can go up to 768 for wide or tall), Restore faces on (using CodeFormer weight 1.0 in Settings), Hires-fix on, to 1024x1024 (double original size) with your preferred upscaler and Denoise 0.4, CFG 7. Then send to img2img!

  2. img2img: DPM++ SED Karras with 20 steps, Restore faces on (CodeFormer weight 1), rescale to 1536x1536, CFG 7, Denoise between 0.3-0.7 (based on how much you want to improve the image), SAME PROMPT! Send to extras when happy with img2img/inpaint results.

  3. extras: Scale to x3 (final will be 4608x4608, I suggest going lower, I did x3 just for the samples here) Upscaler 1 - FatalAnime 4x, Upscaler 2 - SwinIR 4x with 0.10 visibility, GFPGAN 0.10 visibility, CodeFormer 0.10 visibility.

items.name: Love Live! School Idol Festival Cards
items.description:
This LORA aims to replicate the style and layout of Love Live! School Idol Festival Cards and it does so quite well I think.

It's trained on ~3500 card-like images in 512x720 format for 8 epochs.

All example images are made with Anything V3.0.

The trigger word is LLCard
Additionally you should use one of the rarities together with their detail level:

  • N rarity, simple background

  • R rarity, simple background

  • SR rarity, simple background

  • SSR rarity, detailed background

  • UR rarity, detailed background

And lastly use one of the color attributes:

  • pink attribute

  • blue attribute

  • green attribute

Using the name of one of the main cast's girls also replicates them quite well.

This is my first lora so feedback and tips are much appreciated :D

Some issues I am aware of:

  • Smaller CFG Scale creates fancier outfits while bigger CFG creates simpler designs

  • It seems to struggle with hands especially with smaller CFG values

  • The color of the attribute often seems to bleed into eye, hair and clothes colors

  • The small symbol on the bottom right often only shows up after Hires. fixing

  • The names are never readable

items.name: Amazon Muscles
items.description:
It's true, models can already generate muscular people. What this embedding aims to do its reduce changing musculature to a trigger word.

What it's for:

  • Replacing long prompts such as: bodybuilder, thick thighs, muscular thighs, thick arms, muscular arms, thick torso, muscular torso, muscular abs, muscular shoulders, large arms, large thighs, broad shoulders, large torso

  • Making muscular femmes look more feminine. Typically increased prompt words, especially, bodybuilder want to generate masculine features, and put the subject in the gym.

  • Better musculature under clothing.

  • Less extenuated hourglass. Broader torso/abs. For an even bulkier figure, try jujuStyle Lora.

  • More clothes requires more emphasis. See examples for emphasis scaling.

  • Works for anime, and digital painting styles as well.

What it's not for:

  • It can generate masculine subjects, but models typically already do a decent job.

  • Fine-tuning a subject's proportions. Detailed prompting will do better.

items.name: WAS Gunpla
items.description:
WAS Gunpla

A Mobile Suit Gundam Textual Inversion Faux Style

Usage:

Ending your prompt with the following segments is probably the best method. Name may differ for different versions.

  • art by WAS-Gunpla

  • art by [(WAS-Gunpla):0.5] (Less effect)

  • art by (WAS-Gunpla) (More Effect)

  • art by [((WAS-Gunpla)):1.5] (Extreme Ultra Mode)

  • ... etc

Example Positive Prompt(s):

  • ((Close Full Body)) concept of a robot, art by WAS-Gunpla, good hand, best hand, 4k, high-res, masterpiece, best quality

  • ((Close Full Body)) concept of a robot, ((emerging from a dark swamp at night)), art by WAS-Gunpla, good hand, best hand, 4k, high-res, masterpiece, best quality

  • ((Close Full Body)) concept of a ((chrome reflective)) robot, ((in a ruined post apocalypse city)), art by WAS-Gunpla, good hand, best hand, 4k, high-res, masterpiece, best quality

  • ((Close Full Body)) concept of a ((((thin feminine female pink and purple)))) robot, ((floating in space)), art by [(WAS-Gunpla):1], good hand, best hand, 4k, high-res, masterpiece, best quality

Example Negative Prompt(s):

  • ((wood, explosions, fire, wings, tendrils, tentacles, daytime, daylight, bright light, buildings, people, underwater)), NG_DeepNagetive_V1_75T,(greyscale:1.2), ((nude)), paintings, sketches, (worst quality:2), (low quality:2), (normal quality:2), lowres, normal quality, ((monochrome)), ((grayscale))

  • LOFI

  • Basically any fine-tune based on vae-ft-mse-840000-ema-pruned or better

items.name: Sardonyx Blend
items.description:
This is my flagship 'Sardonyx' blend. I find it's in line with what the community on Civit likes producing. It's pretty versatile while also having an artstyle that's unique in image generation.

The mix is incredibly prone to generating NSFW, so you'll need to put more weight on clothing tags and maybe 'nsfw' in your negative prompt. It's also prone to generating see-through shirts a lot, so plan for that I guess.

The blend was made with https://github.com/hako-mikan/sd-webui-supermerger/. I used AOM3 as the base, and it's made up of these LoRA's: Sciamano240, AromaSensei, Robutts, and Shexyo. (All of these LoRA's can be found here on Civit.) The newest version is made with my own AromaSensei LoRA and my new Luminyu LoRA.

I used Hires fix with 4x Fatal Anime 50000 G with 3 Hires Steps, 0.3 denoising strength, and upscaled by 1.5. I use the OrangeMix VAE.

Everything else is specified in the image tags. Make sure to leave a review or a comment if you got good use out of this blend.

items.name: Dark Sakura (Fate Stay Night)
items.description:
V2 Description

Since this is my first Lora ever made and (hopefully) I learned a lot since then I decided to make it again. It's all different training set so result is different too. I think this one is a lot better and in version description I'll list some pros and cons. Also all previews done with weight 1.0 except for closeup which is 0.8.

Basic prompt is now dark sakura, striped dress, hair ribbon.

The red marks now only needs body markings. You don't really have to add it if you're doing the dress unless you want to have a lot of it on legs. It's useful for other outfits through.

For best evil expression use parted lips, evil smile, empty eyes.

Gestures worth a try - hands on own face, hand on own chest, finger on mouth.

V1 Description

This is my first Lora and I'm still not sure what I'm doing but it seems to work fine with weight around 0.7.

Use dark sakura phrase to make it work and also long hair, black dress, red ribbon for the proper look. Adding red eyes and white hair should be unnecessary.

If you're making image with clothes different than original dress, using striped seems to add a stripe pattern similiar to the dress. Also red body markings usually appear with the dress, but for more revealing outfits you will have to use body markings, corruption if you want them to appear in any form other than on the side of the face.

modelVersions.name: V2
modelVersions.description:
Pros over V1:

  • MUCH more malicious expressions

  • Better quality in general, especially comparing on weight 1.0

  • More responsive to poses

  • Less tags needed for basic stuff

  • Trained on her most common gestures like hands on own face, hand on own chest, finger on mouth.

  • Better dress stripes.

Differences:

  • Hair feels longer by default

  • Needs lower weight on closeup because too much malice turns her into a horror.

Cons:

  • Will force dress design more, so you can for example get dress sleeves at other outfits. Requires some effort to go around.

  • Sometimes mouth gets too wide.

LoCon of Super Creek (umamusume)

Please install extension on WebUI.

All of my works is free. If you'd like to support me, feel free to buy me a coffee. 👍

Recommend options

  • LoCon weight around 0.7

  • Trigger words

    • base

      • super creek \(umamusume\)

    • Original racing clothes (SSR stamina) :

      • detached sleeves, long sleeves, bare shoulders, sleeveless sweater, ribbed sweater, white sweater, turtleneck sweater, wrist cuffs, strap between breasts, handbag, shoulder bag, blue dress, thighhighs, zettai ryouiki, thigh boots, mismatched footwear, asysmetrical footwear

    • Racing competition clothes :

      • blue scarf, detached sleeves, bare shoulders, o-ring, clothing cutout, wrist cuffs, scrunchie, strap between breasts, handbag, shoulder bag, blue dress, white skirt, zettai ryouiki, thigh boots

    • Mummy Creek :

      • official alternate costume, halloween costume, mummy costume, ear ornament, choker, cleavage, wrist cuffs, bare shoulders, bandages, bandaged arm, fingernails, nail polish, torn clothes, navel, skirt, frills, bandaged leg

    • Casual clothes :

      • puffy long sleeves, sailor collar, yellow shirt, brown shirt, white shirt, pink bowtie, necklace, belt, pleated skirt, blue skirt, brown footwear, high heel boots

      • (optional) mimikaki

    • Tracen school uniform :

      • white thighhighs, tracen school uniform, purple shirt, pleated skirt, puffy short sleeves, white skirt, puffy sleeves, summer uniform, frilled skirt, sailor collar, sailor shirt, miniskirt, frills

Use animefull based model

  • Settings

    • Stable Diffusion WebUI by Automatic1111

    • DPM++ Series(SDE Karras, 2M Karras, etc.)

    • about 20 steps, CFG scale 3.5~6.5

    • kl-f8-anime2.vae

    • CLIP skip = 1

    • Use Hires.fix to get higher quality image

      • Up-scaler : Latent series

      • Denoising strength 0.50~0.65

LoRA training info

  • trained on sd-scripts by kohya_ss. Thank you a lot!

  • based on Animefull-pruned

  • 134 images of super creek

    • 4x low quality 39 images

    • 8x medium quality 47 images

    • 16x high quality 48 images

    • => 1 epoch = 1300 images

  • replaced character feature tags with super creek \(umamusume\)

    • horse girl, horse tail, brown hair, blue eyes, etc.

  • resolution : 768x768

  • rank=alpha=16

  • conv_rank=conv_alpha=16

  • batch size = 4

  • other training settings is included in training_data.zip

This LoRA may be compatible with animefull-based models (ex. AbyssOrangeMix Series...)

All uploaded images are generated by AOM3A1

Thank you KohakuBlueleaf for introducing LoCon.

And, special thanks to my best friend. DH.

items.name: Midorikawa Hana (Prison School)
items.description:
V2 Description

I'll probably have to redo it sometime in future since I'm not really satisfied, but for now it's an upgrade. Previews have been made with weight 1.0 and it's more compatible thatn V1.

I've changed tagging here to more detailed so now full prompt is midorikawa hana, brown jacket, neck ribbon, collared shirt, school uniform, plaid skirt, loafers.

Additionally:

  • you can optionally add (shorts, shorts under skirt), through you might have to struggle a bit to make them longer like in the series.

  • striped panties works best for underwear ^_^

  • prison clothes, striped shirt, striped pants works for prison outfit, but design is pretty random. Can add midriff if that's what you want. If you get blue stripes on pants (which I'm guessing happens because of panties) you can add blue pants to negatives.

  • eyes looks more generic than V1, but adding squinting helps somewhat. I actually really like V1 eyes, but looking back at the dataset, it was kind of fluke.

  • I recommend trying out ahegao loras with it :D

V1 Description

My second Lora, this time for Hana from Prison School. Seems to work best with weight between 0.7 and 1.0 (lower end for full body).

Add phrase midorikawa hana to make it work. I also add school uniform, shirt for proper clothes. You might have to add brown eyes sometimes if they turn too redish.

modelVersions.name: v2.0 offset
modelVersions.description:
V2.0 is updated! Trained with offset noise, and all demos are generated with Anything V4.5 base model and orange mix VAE.

What this model does: to generate true linearts! (not that manga-like monochrome illustrations)

You can use it without trigger words, but sometimes there will be some unwanted colors, you can use monochrome and lineart to avoid that! (also, remove all colors from your prompt if you don't bother)

And, with the help of ControlNet, you can convert any image into lineart. I made a video to describe the process. If the line is too thin, try lowering the low threshold for the canny preprocessor. Also, you can use multi-ControlNet to assist.

Try applying prompts like sketch or doodles , and you can get a cleaned sketch; by applying chartuner LoRA and openpose helper image, you can get a decent character reference sheet ... this LoRA is full of possibilities!

But sometimes it doesn't go well with character LoRAs, you can either lower the strength of the character LoRA or this LoRA. This LoRA should work fine with a strength of 0.8~1.

Note: since this LoRA is trained based on Anything V4.5, using other base models may have some deteriorations, and you may need to adjust the strength for different base models. Check this reference sheet for different models:

https://imagecache.civitai.com/xG1nkqKTMzGDvpLrqFT7WA/6a8a7f93-32ff-4c9d-9689-197ca1ae7600/width=3968/203078

V2.0已更新，基于offset noise训练，所有展示图片均使用Anything V4.5作为基模，并使用orange mix的VAE。

本模型目的：生成干净的线稿图，而非漫画风黑板图。

正常时无需使用触发词，但有时会出现不想要的颜色，可以使用 monochrome 或 lineart 来加以辅助。

辅以ControlNet，即可将任何图片均转化为线稿风格，我做了一个视频来简单讲解。如果生成的线太细，可以尝试降低canny预处理器的low threshold，也可使用multi-ControlNet来辅助。

使用诸如 sketch 或 doodles 之类的prompt可以生成更干净的草稿风格图片；使用chartuner LoRA和openpose helper image则可以生成人物三视图。本LoRA可玩度很高！

有时使用人物LoRA可能会出现问题，可以通过降低人物LoRA的权重或者降低本LoRA权重来调整效果。本LoRA强度推荐0.8~1。

注：因本模型是基于Anything V4.5进行训练的，故使用其他基模时可能性能会有所下降，可能需要对强度进行调整。下图为不同模型的强度参考：
https://imagecache.civitai.com/xG1nkqKTMzGDvpLrqFT7WA/6a8a7f93-32ff-4c9d-9689-197ca1ae7600/width=3968/203078

items.name: Lily White(リリーホワイト) - Lora - Touhou
items.description:
This is a LoRA model for Lily White from Touhou. After much, much testing and trying to get things working, I finally decided to start sharing LoRAs when I make them. Giving back to the community, or something? Mostly made in an attempt to learn how to train LoRAs, maybe I'll come back and improve on this at some point.

Key Notes:

  • Use "lily_white", "fairy_wings", and maybe "[color] eyes" in your positive prompt for best results.

  • Default should work with her traditional clothes without additional modifiers. Add clothing prompts, and maybe turn down the prompt strength a bit, if you want her wearing something else.

  • Should work on any SD1.5-based model.

  • The example images were upscaled with the following settings on the A1111 Hires. fix: Upscaler: R-ESRGAN 4x+ Anime 6B, Hi-Res Steps: 90, Denoising Strength: 0.2, Upscale by: 2.0

Detailed Notes:

  • Trigger word - "lily_white" - without this, you might get a tiny difference, but the LoRA won't really do a whole lot it in as a prompt. I'll be entirely honest - I'm not sure, exactly, how much much using that as a trigger word in my dataset txt files messes with the results, given that it does sometimes work on its own as a prompt for a lot of models. If anyone has any good reasons for me specifically not to use that sort of thing, and instead use something like "l_w_LoRA" or something of the like, please let me know. Thank you!

  • Training set included multiple eye colors - I've read that her eyes are Green, but each to their own. Put tags like 'green eyes', 'blue eyes', etc. if it isn't coming out how you like. The eye colors in the training set included mostly blue eyes, though some each of red and green, so those three are the most likely eye colors to show up.

  • Her 'main outfit' was in basically every image in the training set, so it'll be the default - adding in additional clothing prompts usually overrides it at 1.0 prompt strength. However, sometimes it doesn't; putting the prompt weight around 0.7-0.8 has had pretty good results for changing the outfit while keeping everything else mostly the same. That said, there have been a few instances where it didn't add her main outfit at usual strength, without modifiers, especially when changing hair styles or specific parts of the outfit - I'd recommend "white dress, long sleeves, white hat, red bow" in your positive prompts, if you're having problems.

  • Most of the training set had her blushing, so that's something of a default, unfortunately. That said, throwing "blush" into the negative prompt does help with it, if it's becoming a problem. I've seen it mess with some emotions, when you try to prompt for them. Sorry!

  • Her wings should come through most of the time, but if they dont, adding 'wings' as a prompt usually fixes it. I swear it's in the data set, despite it not showing up much from my example images!

  • I'd recommend having "detached sleeves" in the negative prompt, unless you like that. I've put probably too much effort trying to weed out the whole "detached sleeves" thing - where a lot of images using this LoRA come out with a hole in the outfit between her shoulders and arms. Unfortunately...I couldn't really fix it. Weird it's cropping up so much, given none of the images in the training set had it...but oh well.

  • The vast majority of my testing has been at 512x512 resolution, other than the 540x860 resolution I used for making example images. I can't promise it'll work amazing on other resolutions. That said, the little testing I did at 540x860 looked pretty alright, so I'm sure it'll probably work for most reasonable resolutions.

  • Haven't tested this with more than a few anime checkpoint models, as I mostly use the BOM sfw; from a little testing, it seems to work well on most of the other orangemix checkpoints and on Anythingv4.0, though as it was trained on SD1.5, it should work on anything based on that. Your results may vary. As an anime character, I've no idea how this will work with realistic models, but I'm sure it would be amusing/terrifying, heh.

Well, I could probably go on with notes, but it's already getting long. Luckily, CivitAI has the "show more/show less". If anyone has any recommendations for tags or anything else I should add here in the notes, please let me know! I'm not really sure what else really needs to go here.

Thanks, and let me know what you think!
